					<description><![CDATA[<p>Nyobolt has earned its unicorn badge officially. They just secured a Series C worth $60 million, and the valuation has risen to $1 billion. The Series C was led by</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/nyobolt-raises-60m-hits-1b-valuation/" data-wpel-link="internal">Nyobolt Raises $60M, Hits $1B Valuation</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="https://nyobolt.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">Nyobolt </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">has earned its unicorn badge officially. They just secured a </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/cellcentric-raises-220m-to-advance-cancer-therapies/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">Series C</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> worth $60 million, and the valuation has risen to $1 billion. The Series C was led by Symotic (NASDAQ: SYM), an AI-enabled robotics company with a focus on supply chains, and heavily backed by IQ Capital, Latitude, Scania Invest and CBMM. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">This new injection of cash pushes Nyobolt’s total raise close to $160 million and hints at the importance of immediate power for the fast-growing autonomous machines and AI data centres.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Solving the Downtime Dilemma</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Dr. Sai Shivareddy and renowned battery scientist Professor Clare Grey founded Nyobolt in 2019 as a spin-out from the University of Cambridge. Nyobolt has resolved one of the most persistent bottlenecks in the tech industry: the slow recharge. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">With its patented niobium-tungsten oxide anodes, Nyobolt&#8217;s batteries can reach 80% in under 5 minutes, something no current lithium-ion cells can do without sacrificing performance.</span></p>
<div id="attachment_200788" style="width: 490px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img fetchpriority="high" decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-200788" class="size-full wp-image-200788" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/nyobolt.jpg" alt="nyobolt" width="480" height="480" /><p id="caption-attachment-200788" class="wp-caption-text">Source: nyobolt<span style="font-size: 16px"> </span></p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">&#8220;Nyobolt is enabling the always-on, always-moving infrastructure that physical AI demands,&#8221; said CEO Sai Shivareddy. &#8220;Enterprises deploying autonomous systems at scale can&#8217;t afford downtime or battery swaps. Our technology allows a new generation of machines to run harder and smarter.&#8221;</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/cellcentric-raises-220m-to-advance-cancer-therapies/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">CellCentric Raises $220M to Advance Cancer Therapies</span></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">A Strategic Alliance with Symbotic</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The amounts invested by Symbotic are no coincidence. Nyobolt’s technology is already integrated into Symbotic’s SymBot&#x2122; autonomous mobile robots. Compared to the ultracapacitors previously used, Nyobolt’s batteries provide six times more energy capacity, are 40% lighter, and boast a cycle life ten times longer than traditional lithium-ion tech. This allows warehouse robots to operate 24/7 with minimal interruption. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">In addition to development work in the warehouse, Nyobolt is starting to tap into the growing market of humanoid robotics (which, as with most new technology, has begun with development of humanoids by the military). </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">According to some sources, the company is working with a major robot manufacturer to improve the work-to-charge ratio of humanoids, whose high energy requirements have traditionally limited their practical use to the battlefield.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Powering the AI Data Centre</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The AI data centre is arguably Nyobolt&#8217;s most important new frontier. Massive GPU clusters powering large-scale AI workloads frequently produce brief power spikes that tax conventional backup systems. Nyobolt’s technology can deliver millisecond response times, acting as a high-density power bridge that ensures stability for mission-critical AI infrastructure.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Looking ahead, Nyobolt is aggressively expanding its global footprint. The company recently signed a Memorandum of Understanding with the state of Rajasthan, India, to deploy over 100MW of off-grid AI data centres and power management systems.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">With revenue growing five times year-on-year, Nyobolt&#8217;s leap to a $1 billion valuation marks a turning point for the UK deep-tech ecosystem, proving that the future of AI isn&#8217;t just about software; it’s about the hardware that keeps it running.</span></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/nyobolt-raises-60m-hits-1b-valuation/" data-wpel-link="internal">Nyobolt Raises $60M, Hits $1B Valuation</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
