					<description><![CDATA[<p>CellCentric has announced its oversubscribed $220m Series D financing, which has just closed. The new cash will enable CellCentric to take Inobrodib into phase III trials, offering hope of the</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/cellcentric-raises-220m-to-advance-cancer-therapies/" data-wpel-link="internal">CellCentric Raises $220M to Advance Cancer Therapies</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="https://www.cellcentric.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">CellCentric </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">has announced its oversubscribed $220m Series D </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/radixark-launches-with-100m-to-power-efficient-ai/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">financing</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">, which has just closed. The new cash will enable CellCentric to take Inobrodib into phase III trials, offering hope of the first new treatment for years for thousands of patients with resistant blood cancers.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The round was led by Venrock Healthcare Capital Partners, one of the larger life sciences investors, with syndicate members Fidelity Management &amp; Research Company, Sofinnova Partners and HBM Healthcare and previous investors RA Capital Management, Forbion and Pfizer.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">A New Frontier in Multiple Myeloma</span></h2>
<p>Inobrodib is a first-in-class oral drug for treating multiple myeloma, a serious plasma cell cancer. The standard of care for myeloma has evolved favourably over the past ten years. However, limited solutions exist for myeloma patients when other treatments fail.</p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Inobrodib exerts its effect by blocking out two proteins known as p300/CBP. They are master switches for the genes that cause cancer. By switching p300/CBP off, the tumour would stop growing and could make the cancer respond to other drugs.</span></p>
<div id="attachment_200784" style="width: 485px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-200784" class="size-full wp-image-200784" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/cellcentric_logo.jpg" alt="cellcentric logo" width="475" height="106" /><p id="caption-attachment-200784" class="wp-caption-text">Source: cellcentric</p></div>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">&#8220;We are thrilled to have the support of top-tier investors who believe in Inobrodib&#8217;s potential.&#8221; &#8220;They believe it can address a critical, growing unmet need,&#8221; said Dr Will West, CEO of CellCentric. &#8220;This funding allows us to move at full speed toward delivering a transformative treatment.&#8221; &#8220;It is for patients who have run out of choices.&#8221;</p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/radixark-launches-with-100m-to-power-efficient-ai/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">RadixArk Launches with $100M to Power Efficient AI</span></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Shifting Care from Hospitals to Homes</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">One of the most distinct advantages of CellCentric’s therapy is its delivery method. Unlike many modern cancer treatments that require intensive hospital-based infusions or specialised monitoring for severe side effects, inobrodib is an oral capsule.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">This &#8220;all-oral&#8221; approach is a potential paradigm shift. </span>It allows patients to manage treatment from home, reducing burden on the healthcare system and families. For roughly 70% of myeloma patients treated in community clinics, this could mean the difference between receiving a life-extending drug or not, due to logistical hurdles.</p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Roadmap to the Market</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The $220 million will be used to fund two pivotal clinical programmes:</span></p>
<ul>
<li style="font-weight: 400"><b>DOMMINO-1:</b><span style="font-weight: 400"> An ongoing Phase 2 study in the UK and US targeting patients who have failed prior intensive therapies.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400"><b>DOMMINO-2:</b><span style="font-weight: 400"> A global Phase 3 trial, slated to begin in the second half of 2026, which will compare Inobrodib combinations against current standard-of-care treatments.</span></li>
</ul>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Initial data presented at the American Society of Haematology (ASH) meeting revealed that inobrodib combined with standard agents generated response rates at least twofold that of historic comparators in heavily pre-treated patients.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">As the biotech industry starts climbing back in 2026, CellCentric&#8217;s megaround can be seen as a vote of confidence in targeted, oral therapies that put clinical benefits and patient QoL ahead.</span></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/cellcentric-raises-220m-to-advance-cancer-therapies/" data-wpel-link="internal">CellCentric Raises $220M to Advance Cancer Therapies</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
