					<description><![CDATA[<p>Enterprise Transformation Shifts Into Multi-Agent AI Systems Tessera Labs has raised $60 million in Series A funding. Andreessen Horowitz led the round. Foundation Capital also participated. Myriad Venture Partners and</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/tessera-labs-raises-60m-to-scale-multi-agent-ai-enterprise-transformation-platform/" data-wpel-link="internal">Tessera Labs Raises $60M To Scale Multi-Agent AI Enterprise Transformation Platform</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<h2><b>Enterprise Transformation Shifts Into Multi-Agent AI Systems</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Tessera Labs has raised $60 million in Series A funding. Andreessen Horowitz led the round. Foundation Capital also participated. Myriad Venture Partners and Osage University Partners joined the raise. The company builds a multi-agent AI platform for enterprise transformation. It focuses on ERP systems and complex business infrastructure.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The funding will support product development and global scaling. It will also expand enterprise sales and AI research teams. Tessera targets large organisations with legacy systems. These systems are often slow and costly to modernise. The company aims to compress transformation timelines significantly.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Seema Amble from Andreessen Horowitz has joined the board. The firm sees Tessera as a shift in enterprise software. It believes AI can remove long transformation cycles. Tessera sits at the centre of this change. It combines </span><a href="https://www.igi-global.com/dictionary/building-situational-applications-for-virtual-enterprises/10003" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">enterprise systems</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> knowledge with autonomous AI execution.</span></p>
<h2><b>Multi-Agent AI Reshapes Enterprise Transformation</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Tessera Labs builds a vendor-agnostic AI platform. It uses multiple AI agents working together. Each agent handles a specific enterprise function. These functions include ERP, CRM, and procurement systems. The system executes transformation across full enterprise stacks.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The platform interprets natural language business requirements. It then converts them into structured system changes. These changes are executed across enterprise environments. Every action is tracked and governed. This ensures control in mission-critical systems.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Traditional ERP transformation takes years to complete. It also requires large consulting teams. Tessera reduces this dependency. It automates coordination across systems and workflows. This reduces both time and cost for enterprises.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The platform is pre-trained on thousands of organisational structures. It understands enterprise patterns across industries. This allows faster adaptation to new environments. It also reduces transformation risk for large organisations.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Many customers operate in regulated industries. These include healthcare, manufacturing, and financial services. These sectors require high levels of governance and auditability. Tessera is designed to meet those requirements.</span></p>
<h2><b>Enterprise Systems Enter an AI-Native Shift</b></h2>
<div id="attachment_200774" style="width: 1322px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-200774" class="size-full wp-image-200774" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/Tessera-2.png" alt="Legacy enterprise ERP systems being transformed by AI automation layers, showing global enterprise modernisation and scalable AI-driven workflows. " width="1312" height="736" /><p id="caption-attachment-200774" class="wp-caption-text">Enterprise systems are entering an AI-native shift, with AI-driven platforms modernising legacy ERP infrastructure, reducing transformation complexity, and enabling faster, more predictable enterprise-wide system upgrades. Source: Created by Ventureburn.</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Enterprise transformation is a large global market. It is valued in the hundreds of billions of dollars. Companies still rely on legacy ERP systems. These systems are expensive to upgrade and maintain.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Tessera targets this structural bottleneck. It uses AI to automate transformation workflows. It also reduces reliance on traditional systems integrators. These firms often manage long transformation programmes.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Andreessen Horowitz led the round due to this opportunity. The firm believes ERP modernisation has been slow for years. It sees Tessera as a new operating model for enterprises.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Seema Amble said ERP systems are critical but outdated. She said transformation has been slow and costly. She added that Tessera introduces predictability into the process. This changes how enterprises approach system upgrades.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company is expanding its engineering and research teams. It is hiring experts in AI systems and enterprise architecture. It is also growing its go-to-market organisation. This supports faster adoption across global markets.</span></p>
