										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Crypto never closes. Bitcoin can move while you sleep, Ethereum can react to ecosystem news before you open your laptop, and altcoins can swing sharply within minutes. For beginners, this creates a familiar problem: the market is full of opportunity, but human attention is limited.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">That is why many beginners search for </span><b>free crypto trading bots</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">, </span><b>AI crypto trading bots</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">, and </span><b>automated crypto trading tools</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> that can monitor the market around the clock. These tools do not generate guaranteed returns but can automate parts of a trading workflow. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">A crypto trading bot automatically monitors markets and executes predefined rules: it watches prices, follows preset rules, and reacts when conditions are met. Some bots are simple grid or DCA tools. Some support copy trading. Some offer no-code automation. Others are fully managed AI systems designed for users who do not want to build strategies themselves.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The goal is to choose a tool that users can understand, test, and manage effectively. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">This guide compares free crypto trading bots in 2026, focusing on features, risks, and beginner use cases. </span></p>
