					<description><![CDATA[<p>LiveEO Expands Its Satellite Monitoring Capability LiveEO has raised more than €28 million in new funding. The company plans to scale its AI-powered monitoring platform. It also plans to grow</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/liveeo-raises-28m/" data-wpel-link="internal">LiveEO Raises €28M To Expand AI Infrastructure Monitoring</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<h2><b>LiveEO Expands Its Satellite Monitoring Capability</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">LiveEO has raised more than €28 million in new funding. The company plans to scale its AI-powered monitoring platform. It also plans to grow its satellite capability. The raise marks the first closing of a larger round that will continue this year.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company builds software that converts satellite images into risk intelligence. It focuses on infrastructure that faces growing climate pressure. It also focuses on networks that require constant monitoring. The platform helps operators detect hazards and prevent costly failures.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The latest funding includes new investors and continued support from earlier backers. LiveEO now exceeds €72 million in total disclosed funding. The company sees this raise as a step toward higher resilience in global infrastructure monitoring.</span></p>
<h2><b>Funding Strengthens AI Platform For Civil Infrastructure</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">LiveEO was founded to address risks linked to ageing infrastructure. Many networks were designed for past climate conditions. Today these conditions have changed. Extreme weather is more frequent. Vegetation spreads faster into power corridors. Ground movement affects rail lines. Manual inspection cannot keep pace.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company uses satellite data to address this gap. Its AI processes images at scale. It identifies risks linked to vegetation, soil movement and external threats. It also supports early warnings that help prevent disruption.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The platform monitors more than one million miles of infrastructure across five continents. Operators receive continuous assessments. These assessments help plan repairs and avoid outages. They also improve long-term safety planning.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">LiveEO plans to grow its civil infrastructure business. This includes wildfire prevention work. It also includes vegetation management and pipeline safety. The new investment allows the company to expand delivery in these areas.</span></p>
<h2><b>Twinspector Constellation Positions LiveEO For Growth<br />
</b></h2>
<div id="attachment_200736" style="width: 1322px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-200736" class="size-full wp-image-200736" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/create-a-futuristic-neon-lit-satellite-m_hkJ9BxXFRBmSAtNZl3tndQ_N15sDWSrT-OqNuruyj_j1Q_cover_hd.png" alt="Satellite constellation capturing high-resolution Earth imagery with AI analyzing infrastructure risks across global networks." width="1312" height="736" /><p id="caption-attachment-200736" class="wp-caption-text">LiveEO’s Twinspector constellation enhances global monitoring with high-resolution imaging and AI-driven risk detection for infrastructure and security. Source: Created by Ventureburn</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">LiveEO gains a key advantage through Twinspector. Twinspector is the company’s own satellite constellation. It was announced earlier in 2026. It supports monitoring at higher resolution. It provides stereo images with up to 35 cm clarity.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">This control helps LiveEO manage its full data pipeline. It no longer depends on external satellite operators. It removes several supply chain risks. It also protects margins and speeds up delivery.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Twinspectors are built for infrastructure analysis. They focus on key risks across transport, utilities and energy. High clarity improves hazard detection. It supports faster response times. It also strengthens the company’s technical lead. The constellation will expand through the new funding. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company plans to improve coverage. It also plans to grow its capacity to support dual-use needs. This includes civil and security customers. The company sees demand increasing for monitoring that helps governments and operators stay ahead of threats. LiveEO positions itself to provide this capability at scale.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News:<a href="https://ventureburn.com/solar-landscape-secures-600-million-to-expand-distributed-energy/" data-wpel-link="internal"> Solar Landscape Secures $600 Million For Distributed Energy Expansion</a></span></p>
<h2><b>Growing Demand For Dual-Use Security And Defence Solutions</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">LiveEO is expanding into security markets as demand rises. Many customers seek intelligence that helps detect border risks. Many also seek tools that improve protection for critical sites. This demand has grown due to global instability. It has also grown due to pressure on national infrastructure.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">LiveEO’s technology supports surveillance and reconnaissance. It provides insights based on satellite imagery and AI. It offers operators clear indicators of change. It supports long-term safety planning. The company believes this area will grow sharply over the next few years.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The new funding helps LiveEO build this pipeline. It also supports work with clients that need secure and reliable image analysis. The company will continue investing in its research and engineering teams. It also plans to expand customer delivery functions.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">LiveEO continues to build partnerships with infrastructure owners. It also grows relationships with public and enterprise customers. Its technology is used in rail networks, energy corridors and pipelines. It expects greater adoption as </span><a href="https://www.studysmarter.co.uk/explanations/environmental-science/agriculture-and-forestry/climate-impact/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">climate impact</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> and security threats rise.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">To stay updated on crypto venture capital funding and market trends, visit our </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/category/news/venture-capital/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">venture capital news section</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> for more insights.</span></p>
