					<description><![CDATA[<p>Signadori Bio, a preclinical-stage biopharmaceutical company developing a novel platform of &#8220;off-the-shelf&#8221; immunotherapies, announced the closing an €11 million ($11.9 million) seed extension financing round. The capital raised will be</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/signadori-bio-raises-e11m-to-advance-tumour-platform/" data-wpel-link="internal">Signadori Bio Raises €11M to Advance Tumour Platform</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="https://www.signadoribio.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">Signadori Bio</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">, a preclinical-stage biopharmaceutical company developing a novel platform of &#8220;off-the-shelf&#8221; immunotherapies, announced the closing an €11 million ($11.9 million) seed extension </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/radixark-launches-with-100m-to-power-efficient-ai/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">financing </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">round.</span></p>
<p>The capital raised will be used to advance the company&#8217;s proprietary in vivo monocyte engineering platform for treating solid tumours. Led by Taiho Ventures and returning investors Sofinnova Partners and Invivo Partners, the Series A tranche extends funding to achieve milestones over 18 months.</p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">A Radical Shift: Reprogramming the Innate Immune System</span></h2>
<section class="text-token-text-primary w-full focus:outline-none [--shadow-height:45px] has-data-writing-block:pointer-events-none has-data-writing-block:-mt-(--shadow-height) has-data-writing-block:pt-(--shadow-height) [&amp;:has([data-writing-block])&gt;*]:pointer-events-auto [content-visibility:auto] supports-[content-visibility:auto]:[contain-intrinsic-size:auto_100lvh] R6Vx5W_threadScrollVars scroll-mb-[calc(var(--scroll-root-safe-area-inset-bottom,0px)+var(--thread-response-height))] scroll-mt-[calc(var(--header-height)+min(200px,max(70px,20svh)))]" dir="auto" data-turn-id="request-69984495-12c8-8328-bd29-940638b034c4-5" data-testid="conversation-turn-2" data-scroll-anchor="false" data-turn="assistant">
<div class="text-base my-auto mx-auto pb-10 [--thread-content-margin:var(--thread-content-margin-xs,calc(var(--spacing)*4))] @w-sm/main:[--thread-content-margin:var(--thread-content-margin-sm,calc(var(--spacing)*6))] @w-lg/main:[--thread-content-margin:var(--thread-content-margin-lg,calc(var(--spacing)*16))] px-(--thread-content-margin)">
<div class="[--thread-content-max-width:40rem] @w-lg/main:[--thread-content-max-width:48rem] mx-auto max-w-(--thread-content-max-width) flex-1 group/turn-messages focus-visible:outline-hidden relative flex w-full min-w-0 flex-col agent-turn">
<div class="flex max-w-full flex-col gap-4 grow">
<div class="min-h-8 text-message relative flex w-full flex-col items-end gap-2 text-start break-words whitespace-normal outline-none keyboard-focused:focus-ring [.text-message+&amp;]:mt-1" dir="auto" data-message-author-role="assistant" data-message-id="331724b1-7198-457a-aaf8-1d686f89b1ed" data-message-model-slug="gpt-5-3" data-turn-start-message="true">
<div class="flex w-full flex-col gap-1 empty:hidden">
<div class="markdown prose dark:prose-invert w-full wrap-break-word dark markdown-new-styling">
<p data-start="0" data-end="147" data-is-last-node="" data-is-only-node="">While CAR-T therapies have seen success in blood cancers, they struggle against solid tumours due to the immunosuppressive tumour microenvironment. Signadori Bio is taking a different approach by focusing on monocytes, the &#8220;first responders&#8221; of the innate immune system.</p>
<div id="attachment_200726" style="width: 490px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-200726" class="size-full wp-image-200726" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/Signadori-Bio-1.jpg" alt="Signadori Bio" width="480" height="145" /><p id="caption-attachment-200726" class="wp-caption-text">Source: Signadori Bio</p></div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</section>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company’s platform leverages a breakthrough discovery involving the p21 protein (encoded by the </span><i><span style="font-weight: 400">CDKN1A</span></i><span style="font-weight: 400"> gene). Research conducted at Gustave Roussy, Europe’s leading oncology center, identified p21 as a master regulator of myeloid anti-tumour functions. </span>Signadori’s technology allows in vivo reprogramming of these cells, turning them into potent anti-cancer agents that infiltrate the TME.</p>
<p>“This financing represents an important milestone as we advance our platform toward the clinic,” said Dr Selwyn Ho. “Our approach to in vivo engineering has the potential to unlock immunotherapies more accessible and scalable than current autologous cell therapies.”</p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/radixark-launches-with-100m-to-power-efficient-ai/?amp=1" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">RadixArk Launches with $100M to Power Efficient AI</span></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Strategic Growth and Clinical Roadmap</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The proceeds from the €11 million round will be deployed toward three primary objectives:</span></p>
<ol>
<li style="font-weight: 400"><b>Lead Candidate Nomination:</b><span style="font-weight: 400"> Advancing the company&#8217;s flagship program, SiB-2101, toward official lead candidate status.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400"><b>Platform Expansion:</b><span style="font-weight: 400"> Further refining the proprietary delivery and engineering mechanisms that allow monocytes to be modified directly within the patient’s bloodstream.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400"><b>Team Scaling:</b><span style="font-weight: 400"> Expanding the company’s scientific and operational footprint at The HIVE Innovation Center in Villejuif, located within the prestigious Paris-Saclay Cancer Cluster.</span></li>
</ol>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The addition of Taiho Ventures brings significant strategic value, given Taiho’s global expertise in oncology. &#8220;Signadori Bio is advancing a highly differentiated strategy by targeting monocytes and leveraging in vivo engineering&#8221;, noted Seiji Miyahara, Partner at Taiho Ventures. &#8220;The company’s compelling preclinical data positions it well to address significant unmet needs in solid tumours.&#8221;</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Leadership Transition</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The funding follows the recent appointment of Dr Selwyn Ho as CEO in March 2026. Dr Ho, with nearly 30 years’ experience in immuno-oncology, took over from Matthieu Coutet, now chair of the board. This leadership shift signals Signadori’s transition from a discovery-phase venture to a development-focused biotech firm.</span></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/signadori-bio-raises-e11m-to-advance-tumour-platform/" data-wpel-link="internal">Signadori Bio Raises €11M to Advance Tumour Platform</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
